<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-03-12T19:29:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-03-12T19:29:00-05:00" n="581" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d581">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 337.11/268</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Habana</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-03-12T19:00:00-05:29">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March, 12, 1917, 7 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>American administrator of Punta Alegra Sugar Mills, Camaguey, belong to
                            Atkins, together with Lieutenant of Federal forces, went to meet rebel
                            leader to receive his surrender. Neither have returned. Atkins says
                            rebels [omission] as ransom. Have notified naval commander and Cuban
                            Government has sent two detachments cavalry.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Gonzales</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>